This paper deals with the secure transmission of information over a wire-tap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on the use of multiple antennas at different terminals, which is a common theme in wireless communication research. The paper also discusses the use of cooperative jamming, which is a technique used to improve the security of wireless transmissions, and is therefore relevant to the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses various signal processing techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
